Actually, they went both ways.

> There is a 1913 KRIT in the National Automobile Museum in Reno, NV.  The
> KRIT is the first car you see when you enter the collection; it is a
> beautiful car.  People are constantly insisting that the insignia on the
> radiator offends them and demand that the car be removed.

We had a similar hue and cry here when somebody realized that some of the
folks at Van Nuys airport flying military trainers had a couple in WWII
Luftwaffe livery.  They had been that way for a decade!

> The collection also has a marvelous red 64 Beetle convertible.

I remember it from its heyday as "Harrah's Automobile Collection".  It
took two days to get through it back then, but they sold off a lot of the
vehicles.  Bill Harrah insisted that all the vehicles on display be
drivable.

